WEBVTT

00:00.078 --> 00:02.851
<i>The '80s was the
golden age of the house party.</i>

00:02.945 --> 00:05.031
<i>If the music was cranked
and the place was wrecked,</i>

00:05.101 --> 00:06.424
<i>your bash was a hit.</i>

00:06.500 --> 00:08.757
<i>And it turned out I had
a hot tip about the latest one.</i>

00:08.850 --> 00:10.623
Yo, J.C., it's me, Adam.

00:10.702 --> 00:12.669
- Corey's brother!
- Not even a little bit.

00:12.704 --> 00:14.971
Anyway, I thought
you'd want to know about a rager

00:15.073 --> 00:16.539
at Dave Kim's this Saturday.

00:16.641 --> 00:17.830
Let all your bros know.

00:17.855 --> 00:18.851
Will do.

00:18.876 --> 00:20.642
Tell Corey he's a dirty dog.

00:20.711 --> 00:23.645
<i>I'd fed the grapevine a grape.
Only thing left to do was wait.</i>

00:23.714 --> 00:25.447
Party at Dave Kim's this Saturday.

00:25.549 --> 00:27.883
If there's no hot tub, we'll make one.

00:27.952 --> 00:29.651
Party at Dave Kim's this Saturday.

00:29.753 --> 00:30.953
There's gonna be 50 kegs,

00:31.055 --> 00:33.689
and Spuds MacKenzie is deejaying.

00:33.791 --> 00:35.524
Party at Dave Kim's this Saturday.

00:35.593 --> 00:37.226
I'll know if you don't show.

00:37.294 --> 00:39.394
Hubba Bubba Soda? Do better.

00:39.496 --> 00:40.896
<i>Word about the party spread fast,</i>

00:40.965 --> 00:42.431
<i>until everyone knew about it.</i>

00:42.466 --> 00:43.866
Party at Dave Kim's this Saturday.

00:43.968 --> 00:45.300
<i>Well, almost everyone.</i>

00:45.402 --> 00:46.501
What the hell?!

00:46.570 --> 00:48.270
Who's telling everybody
I'm throwing a party?

00:48.339 --> 00:50.105
They're the worst. And it's me.

00:50.174 --> 00:51.373
You?! Why?!

00:51.475 --> 00:52.808
Come on, Dave Kim!

00:52.877 --> 00:54.443
No one loves a kegger more than you.

00:54.545 --> 00:55.577
And it's a keg party?

00:55.646 --> 00:57.479
Yep, all kinds of savory brewskis...

00:57.581 --> 01:00.048
ales, lights, fruity ciders,
light beers.

01:00.150 --> 01:01.350
No, wait. Those are the lights.

01:01.418 --> 01:02.584
You don't know anything about beer!

01:02.653 --> 01:04.119
I do know your parents are out of town,

01:04.188 --> 01:07.055
and kegs attract popular kids,
and that's what I'm looking for.

01:07.124 --> 01:08.156
Is this about Brea Bee?

01:08.259 --> 01:09.725
Yes, it's about Brea Bee.

01:09.793 --> 01:11.426
I know we had a moment
while ice-skating,

01:11.495 --> 01:12.828
but I've barely seen her since.

01:12.897 --> 01:14.363
Now she's back to her ivory tower

01:14.465 --> 01:16.064
with the cool kids across the room.

01:16.133 --> 01:19.301
So you think that a party that
will inevitably destroy my home

01:19.370 --> 01:21.837
is just the opportunity you need
to reconnect?

01:21.872 --> 01:23.538
Will you help your best friend
find love?

01:23.641 --> 01:24.539
Hell no.

01:24.608 --> 01:25.941
I hear we're throwing a party.

01:25.976 --> 01:27.376
Oh, no! Carla's got wind of it!

01:27.478 --> 01:28.644
Bitch, I am the wind.

01:28.712 --> 01:31.647
And I've already got a theme...
mayhem and deep regret.

01:31.715 --> 01:34.716
Oh, no! That's a winner!
Who wouldn't come to that?

01:34.785 --> 01:36.451
I would, and hopefully so will Brea.

01:36.553 --> 01:37.819
Someone's a nasty boy.

01:37.888 --> 01:39.821
Ugh. It's lunchtime.

01:39.890 --> 01:42.524
I'm supposed to open
the wing store today!

01:42.593 --> 01:43.992
Why are you doing this to me?!

01:44.094 --> 01:45.494
Brea Bee is just a girl!

01:45.529 --> 01:47.162
Just a girl, Dave Kim?

01:47.231 --> 01:49.767
She's gorgeous, cool, and likes theater.

01:50.901 --> 01:52.768
Well, looks like your perfect dream girl

01:52.836 --> 01:54.403
just dropped her Trapper Keeper.

01:56.640 --> 01:57.906
Allow me, madam.

01:57.975 --> 01:59.308
Oh. Thanks, Adam.

01:59.410 --> 02:01.510
Ohh! Thank you.

02:01.578 --> 02:03.578
...in advance for my next question.

02:03.647 --> 02:06.114
Which is, if you had to pick one word

02:06.216 --> 02:08.183
to describe how you party,

02:08.285 --> 02:09.717
would it be "hardy"?

02:10.654 --> 02:12.754
Like Dave Kim's party... this Saturday.

02:12.823 --> 02:13.922
Oh! T-That might be fun.

02:13.991 --> 02:16.525
It's guaranteed to be a blast.
I'm planning it myself.

02:16.593 --> 02:17.893
I want to plan.

02:17.962 --> 02:19.928
The best part of partying is
the who, what, when, and where.

02:19.997 --> 02:21.129
Mm. With a little foresight,

02:21.231 --> 02:23.065
planning a party can be
as fun as attending.

02:23.100 --> 02:25.033
I'm pretty sure
me and Brea got it covered.

02:25.102 --> 02:26.535
Say, my place around 4:00?

02:26.603 --> 02:27.669
It's a date.

02:27.738 --> 02:29.738
Yeah, sorry. I actually
can't do it today.

02:29.807 --> 02:31.006
But I'll try to make the party.

02:31.108 --> 02:33.008
I know a solid maybe when I hear one.

02:33.077 --> 02:34.643
Whoa. Think she likes you.

02:34.745 --> 02:35.644
- Really?
- No.

02:35.746 --> 02:37.312
But now this won't feel so lousy.

02:37.414 --> 02:40.015
Oh, no! Wait! This is why you
don't put yourself out there!

02:40.084 --> 02:41.883
Oh, balls!

02:41.986 --> 02:43.552
♪ I'm twisted up inside ♪

02:43.654 --> 02:47.065
♪ But nonetheless,
I feel the need to say ♪

